Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss cauliflower and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, half the @Blackening Spice{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until veggies are slightly charred and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve @jalapeño{1} lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; thinly slice into half-moons. Thinly slice @radishes{3}. Zest and halve @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.

While veggies roast, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine jalapeño, radishes, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, half the cilantro, half the lime zest, juice from remaining lime, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and salt and pepper to taste.

In a second small #bowl{}, combine @vegan chipotle mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, and a pinch of lime zest to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Once veggies are done roasting, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates. Spread half the chipotle-lime mayo in a line across the center of tortillas; fill with cabbage slaw (draining first) and roasted veggies.

Top tacos with @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, remaining chipotle-lime mayo, and as many pickled veggies (draining first) as you like. Garnish with remaining cilantro and serve.

> Add beef or turkey to tacos along with cabbage slaw and roasted veggies.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.